    "reasoning": "To implement the 12-hour clock module, we must manage three counters for hours, minutes, and seconds, all operating in BCD format. The clock resets to 12:00:00 AM upon reset assertion. The hour counter ranges from 1 to 12, with 'pm' indicating afternoon. Seconds and minutes range from 00 to 59. Sequential logic is triggered on the positive edge of clk. The reset has higher priority than enable, so when reset is high, the counters are reset regardless of ena. We will use three separate counters for hh, mm, and ss, updating them sequentially. Since all counters are in BCD, we need to ensure valid BCD representations at every step. The logic should check for rollovers: seconds roll over to 00 when reaching 60, minutes roll over when seconds hit 60, and hours roll over when minutes hit 60. Hours also need to toggle between AM and PM correctly. The implementation uses a single always block for updating all counters with proper synchronization and reset handling. BCD checks are important to ensure valid values.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input reset,\n    input ena,\n    output pm,\n    output [7:0] hh,\n    output [7:0] mm,\n    output [7:0] ss\n);\n\n    // Internal signals\n    logic [7:0] hh_reg;\n    logic [7:0] mm_reg;\n    logic [7:0] ss_reg;\n    logic pm_reg;\n\n    // Sequential logic\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (reset) begin\n            hh_reg <= 8'h12;\n            mm_reg <= 8'h00;\n            ss_reg <= 8'h00;\n            pm_reg <= 1'b0;\n        end\n        else if (ena) begin\n            // Increment seconds\n            if (ss_reg == 8'h59) begin\n                ss_reg <= 8'h00;\n                // Increment minutes\n                if (mm_reg == 8'h59) begin\n                    mm_reg <= 8'h00;\n                    // Increment hours\n                    if (hh_reg == 8'h12) begin\n                        hh_reg <= 8'h1;\n                        pm_reg <= ~pm_reg; // Toggle AM/PM\n                    end\n                    else begin\n                        hh_reg <= hh_reg + 1;\n                    end\n                end\n                else begin\n                    mm_reg <= mm_reg + 1;\n                end\n            end\n            else begin\n                ss_reg <= ss_reg + 1;\n            end\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Assign outputs\n    assign pm = pm_reg;\n    assign hh = hh_reg;\n    assign mm = mm_reg;\n    assign ss = ss_reg;\n\nendmodule"
}
